This defines the form the developer sees.

45
04:24:00,000 --> 04:30:00,000
Parameter one. Service Information.
Required fields. Name, team, description.

46
04:30:00,000 --> 04:36:00,000
Service name must be lowercase, hyphens only.
Example. fraud-detection, payment-processor, risk-api.

47
04:36:00,000 --> 04:42:00,000
Team is an OwnerPicker field. It pulls from the catalog.
The developer selects their team.

48
04:42:00,000 --> 04:48:00,000
Description is a text area for one sentence.
Language defaults to Python. Options are Python, Go, and Node.js.

49
04:48:00,000 --> 04:54:00,000

50
04:54:00,000 --> 05:00:00,000
Parameter two. Infrastructure Configuration.

51
05:00:00,000 --> 05:06:00,000
Traffic tier. Low, medium, or high.
Low means less than one thousand requests per day.
Medium means one thousand to one hundred thousand requests per day.
High means more than one hundred thousand requests per day.

52
05:06:00,000 --> 05:12:00,000
Needs database. Boolean. Creates an RDS t4g.micro with stop and start schedule.
Needs cache. Boolean. Creates an ElastiCache t4g.micro node.

53
05:12:00,000 --> 05:18:00,000
Needs S3. Boolean. Creates an S3 bucket with lifecycle policy.
Defaults to true.

54
05:18:00,000 --> 05:24:00,000
Environment. Dev, staging, or production. Defaults to dev.

55
05:24:00,000 --> 05:30:00,000

56
05:30:00,000 --> 05:36:00,000
Parameter three. Cost Estimate and Confirmation.
A description explains that the estimate is based on selections
and assumes standard FinOps optimization profile.

57
05:36:00,000 --> 05:42:00,000
A checkbox confirms the developer has reviewed the cost estimate.
They must check it to proceed.

58
05:42:00,000 --> 05:48:00,000

59
05:48:00,000 --> 05:54:00,000
