09:12:00,000 --> 09:18:00,000
First, the Dockerfile skeleton.

94
09:18:00,000 --> 09:24:00,000
For Python, use python three point eleven slim bookworm.
Multi-stage build. Builder stage installs dependencies.
Runtime stage copies the installed packages and runs as non-root user.

95
09:24:00,000 --> 09:30:00,000
The runtime stage creates an appuser with user ID one thousand.
It sets environment variables to disable bytecode compilation and enable unbuffered output.

96
09:30:00,000 --> 09:36:00,000
It exposes port eight thousand.
It adds a healthcheck that curls the health endpoint.
It runs uvicorn with two workers.

97
09:36:00,000 --> 09:42:00,000
For Go, use golang one point twenty-two alpine.
Builder stage downloads modules and compiles a static binary.
Runtime stage uses gcr.io/distroless static for the smallest possible image.

98
09:42:00,000 --> 09:48:00,000
For Node.js, use node twenty alpine.
Production stage uses npm ci dash dash only production.
Runs as non-root user.

99
09:48:00,000 --> 09:54:00,000

100
09:54:00,000 --> 10:00:00,000
Second, the Helm values.yaml skeleton.

101
10:00:00,000 --> 10:06:00,000
Replica count is set by traffic tier.
Image repository is a placeholder. GitHub Actions will set it.

102
10:06:00,000 --> 10:12:00,000
Resource requests and limits are set by traffic tier.
Low traffic. One hundred millicpu. Two hundred fifty-six megabytes.
Two hundred millicpu limit. Five hundred twelve megabytes limit.

103
10:12:00,000 --> 10:18:00,000
Medium traffic. Five hundred millicpu. One gigabyte.
One thousand millicpu limit. Two gigabyte limit.

104
10:18:00,000 --> 10:24:00,000
High traffic. Two thousand millicpu. Four gigabytes.
Four thousand millicpu limit. Eight gigabyte limit.

105
10:24:00,000 --> 10:30:00,000

106
10:30:00,000 --> 10:36:00,000
If use_spot is true, add Spot tolerations.
Tolerations for capacity-type spot and dedicated application.
Node selector prefers ARM64 architecture for twenty percent additional savings.

107
10:36:00,000 --> 10:42:00,000
Affinity prefers Spot instances with weight eighty.
On-Demand fallback with weight twenty.

108
10:42:00,000 --> 10:48:00,000

109
10:48:00,000 --> 10:54:00,000
If use_spot is false, use On-Demand only.
Pod anti-affinity spreads replicas across availability zones.

110
10:54:00,000 --> 11:00:00,000

111
11:00:00,000 --> 11:06:00,000
If HPA is enabled for high traffic services, configure autoscaling.
Min replicas equals replica count. Max replicas equals ten.
Target CPU utilization seventy percent.
Target memory utilization eighty percent.

112
11:06:00,000 --> 11:12:00,000
Scale down behavior. Stabilization window five minutes.
Remove one pod per minute.
Scale up behavior. Stabilization window thirty seconds.
Add two pods per thirty seconds.

113
11:12:00,000 --> 11:18:00,000

114
11:18:00,000 --> 11:24:00,000
Third, the catalog-info.yaml skeleton.

115
11:24:00,000 --> 11:30:00,000
Annotations include GitHub project slug, ArgoCD app name,
