spot-enabled if applicable, PostgreSQL if needed, Redis if needed.

118
11:42:00,000 --> 11:48:00,000

119
11:48:00,000 --> 11:54:00,000
Fourth, the GitHub Actions CI skeleton.

120
11:54:00,000 --> 12:00:00,000
The workflow has three jobs. Test, security, and build.

121
12:00:00,000 --> 12:06:00,000
The test job installs dependencies and runs tests.
For Python, it runs ruff, mypy, and pytest with coverage.
For Go, it runs go vet and go test.
For Node.js, it runs npm test.

122
12:06:00,000 --> 12:12:00,000

123
12:12:00,000 --> 12:18:00,000
The security job runs gitleaks for secret scanning.
It runs Trivy for filesystem vulnerability scanning.
It uploads results to GitHub Security tab.

124
12:18:00,000 --> 12:24:00,000

125
12:24:00,000 --> 12:30:00,000
The build job runs only on pushes to main.
It configures AWS credentials using OIDC.
It logs into ECR.
It sets up QEMU for multi-arch builds.

126
12:30:00,000 --> 12:36:00,000
It sets up Docker Buildx.
It builds and pushes a multi-arch image.
Platforms are linux/amd64 and linux/arm64.
This enables Graviton Spot instances.

127
12:36:00,000 --> 12:42:00,000
It scans the container image with Trivy.
It updates the Helm values.yaml file with the new image tag.
It commits and pushes the change with skip ci in the commit message.

128
12:42:00,000 --> 12:48:00,000
The skip ci flag prevents an infinite loop of CI runs.

